1. Investigation objective

You are trying to prove or disprove these competing models:

Model A

PX slave / PX allocation failure happens first
→ ORA-12805
→ domain reconfig
→ PDB/service churn on 3/4 as fallout

Model B

RAC domain / IPC / inter-instance instability happens first
→ PX slaves become unreachable
→ ORA-12805
→ PDB/service churn follows

Model C

PDB/service/GDS movement on instances 3/4 starts first
→ sessions/services get disrupted
→ PX/GV$ monitoring workload hits broken path
→ ORA-12805 + domain churn

Model D

Instance 3 or 4 becomes locally degraded first
→ PX pool/service/PDB state collapses there
→ RAC/PX symptoms cascade

Do not start with conclusions. Start with evidence to separate these.

⸻

2. The five investigation lanes

Run the RCA in five lanes, then merge by timestamp.

Lane A

SQL / PX / session lane
What SQL ran, where, with what DOP, and which slaves died.

Lane B

RAC / domain / cluster lane
Did domain churn start first, or react to PX failure.

Lane C

OS / IPC / process / network lane
Was there a node-local or transport anomaly on instance 3/4.

Lane D

Scope / blast radius lane
Is this one DB only, one PDB group only, or broader cluster impact.

Lane E

PDB / service / GDS / open-close lane
Are PDB and service movements on 3/4 causal, downstream, or just noise.

